**Understanding the Problem: Why Thresholds Matter**

Your line-following bot uses sensors to "see" the line. These sensors don't give you a simple "line/no line" signal. They give you a *value* – usually a reading of reflectance (how much light is reflected). The threshold is the value you set to decide whether the sensor "sees" the line or not.

*   **Too Low Threshold:**  If your threshold is too low, even slightly darker surfaces or shadows can be interpreted as the line, causing unwanted turns. This is the *most common* cause of random turning.
*   **Too High Threshold:** If your threshold is too high, the sensor might not recognize the line at all, or only recognize very bright, very well-defined lines.

